history.text: Hi have you seen Catch Me If You Can?
Staring Leonardo DiCaprio
I have! I thought the comedy in it was balanced really well with the serious aspects
It got pretty good reviews, but that's expected considering the cast and being directed by spielberg
The story is pretty impressive, that Frank started committing fraud with success at such a young age
Oh for sure, It's been years since I last watched it but I remember the main characters being extremely clever and likable.
I remember thinking that there's no way anyone would be able to get away with such crimes these days.
After the FBI recruited him I'm sure he had a lot of information to give them to secure the system
Seems like he still made off pretty easy in the end
Yes true, I remember the scene of him printing out the forged checks on a giant machine.
I did not realize that Frank was only 19 while performing his cons.
You'd think a person would need to be middle aged to impersonate a doctor or lawyer.
Yeah. You have to be pretty confident in yourself to put yourself out there like that
I always wondered why Frank Sr. was denied the business loan at the beginning of the film
Me too, but I always over think details of the story, maybe it doesn't matter in the grand scheme of things and Frank was destined to become a conman anyway!
That's a good point
Do you watch many biographic movies?
Probably not more than other genres, but I like learning about the lives of people and their differences
Which actor/actress woudl you say is your favorite in the movie? I really liked Hanks performance
DiCaprio, he's my favorite actor. I've seen nearly all of his films.
I don't often like stories about broken families, but there's so many interesting elements to this story that it outshines the bits I don't like.
Yeah. it really felt like he made the "best" of his situation
I wonder if he felt more trapped in prison or "working" for the FBI
That's one way of putting it. I don't think I have the chops to impersonate any skilled profession, especially well enough to not be caught while making money
I think working for the FBI he could probably run scams in prison
very true

It seems like he was kind of in the right place at the right time and interacted with just the right people to get where he is today. Any earlier and he may have rotted in prison, later and someone else could h
ave developed  the security checks
Too true. Interesting how the story follows the line of "it takes a thief to catch a thief"
The ratings seem to be pretty consistent, do you value any of the three shown more than another?
Perhaps rotten tomatoes.
I think their ratings are consistent and true
though I find that they tend to rate horror movies too low.
I prefer Metacritic, but I've known of rotten tomatoes for a long time so still take their scores into account, even if I don't read the actual review
I used to take the time out to read some of the reviews but I like diving in and enjoying the story with fresh eyes.
Yeah, same. Too many spoiled movies from reading stuff online.
I think I'll watch Cat Me If You Can again today since it's been so long since I watched it originally
Is... Is this the end?
I'm not sure
the finish convo thing is selectable now.. think I'm going to try.
It was fun talking. hope you enjoy the movie is you watch it
Ah thx you too

uid2response.feedback: The document helped but not enough to give the users interesting enough talking points.
